               <head>Nizami’s masnavi, Makhzan al-asrar</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Makhzan al-asrār by Niẓāmī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1124A-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_2474895">Niẓāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_2474895">نظامى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3764">Makhzan al-asrār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_3764">مخزن الاسرار</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>First mas̲navī from the collection of allegorical and Ṣūfī-inspired quintet or <title>Khamsah</title> of poems by <persName key="person_2474895" role="aut">Ilyās Abū Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf ibn Muʿayyid Ganjaʾī</persName> (d. 599/1203). 

                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 107v): completed by … (scribe and place name erased), 22 Z̲ī al-Qaʿd[ah] 1[0]89/5 January 1679. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Frequent detailed annotations and corrections in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped and Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Binding damaged, boards covered with marbled paper and brown leather edging; marbling delaminating and torn, exposing inner matter (<title>Qurʾān</title> fragment; Persian correspondence). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dust wrapper over text block, Oriental paper. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition very fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
